      "text": "It is often assumed that in a commons people share purpose and values at the very outset. This might be true for [[intentional communities]] and some [[cooperatives]], but commons often come about because people live in a shared space, make use of the same resource-system or infrastructure, or simply because they share a problem that they know won't solved individually. "
